RotateText - draw text at any angle using OpenGL 2.0

========================================================================
Sample Description:

 The RotateText sample is an application that shows how to render 
 any text using OpenGL (feature many times requested at forums).
 Basically the app adds new function render_text_angle() to bbutil.c.

 When you run the application, you will see rotating text.

 Feature summary
 - Initializing and rendering to OpenGL 2.0 
 - Drawing text at any angle

========================================================================
Requirements:

 - BlackBerry Native SDK for Tablet OS 2.0 or later
 - One of the following:
   - BlackBerry PlayBook tablet running BlackBerry Tablet OS 2.0 or later
   - BlackBerry Tablet Simulator 2.0 or later
   - BlackBerry10 Device Alpha
   - BlackBerry10 Simulator

========================================================================
Importing a project into the Native SDK:

 1. File->New->Blackberry Tablet OS C/C++ Project
 2. In 'Project name' field type in 'RotateTexxt'. Press Next.
 3. Select 'Language:' C, 'Build Style:' Managed, 'Project Type:' Empty Application.
    Press 'Finish'.
 4. Right click on this Project's src folder in Project Explorer and choose Import...
 5. Choose 'File system' and add files main.c, bbutil_bg.c, bbutil_bg.h from this repository. Hit Finish.
 6. Right click on this Project in Project Explorer and choose Properties.
 7. In 'Configuration:' choose preferable configuration (Simulator- or Device-Debug).
 8. Under C/C++ Build->Settings->QCC Compiler->Defines (-D) add USING_GL20 
 8. Under C/C++ Build->Settings->QCC Linker->Libraries add following libraries in
    'Libraries (-l)' section: bps, screen, EGL, GLESv2, freetype, png, m. Click OK.
 9. Build and deploy.
